<HH> ============= Screen: Intervention strategies ============== </HH>

<Vertical id="fba2_intervention_strategies">
<Markdown>
## Intervention Strategies

Below are strategies for addressing problem behaviors. For each strategy, select which **function of behavior** it addresses. Remember: Johnny's function is **escape**, so we need to identify which strategies target escape.
</Markdown>

<CapaProblem id="fba2_antecedent_strategies_problem" title="Antecedent Strategies">
<Markdown>### Antecedent Strategies (to prevent the problem behavior)</Markdown>
<TabularMCQGrader>
  <TabularMCQ id="fba2_antecedent_strategies">
cols: Escape, Attention, Sensory, Tangible
rows:
  - "Use sensory-friendly relaxation techniques before bed|relaxation[Sensory]"
  - "Create a predictable bedtime routine to make bedtime more manageable and less aversive|routine[Escape]"
  - "Give high-quality attention before bed|attention_before[Attention]"
  - "Use timers and advance warnings to make bedtime more predictable|timers[Escape]"
  - "Give the child a stuffed animal before they get into bed|stuffed_animal[Tangible]"
  - "Have the child engage in yoga right before bedtime|yoga[Sensory]"
  </TabularMCQ>
</TabularMCQGrader>
</CapaProblem>

<CapaProblem id="fba2_consequence_strategies_problem" title="Consequence Strategies">
<Markdown>### Consequence Strategies (to react to the problem behavior)</Markdown>
<TabularMCQGrader>
  <TabularMCQ id="fba2_consequence_strategies">
cols: Escape, Attention, Sensory, Tangible
rows:
  - "Provide extra attention during bedtime refusal behaviors|extra_attention[Attention]"
  - "Teach the child to use a bedtime pass — one approved brief delay per night|bedtime_pass[Escape]"
  - "Talk to the child until they eventually go to sleep|talk_sleep[Attention]"
  - "Give the child access to an iPad when they successfully get in bed|ipad_reward[Tangible]"
  - "Ignore behaviors such as whining that serve to delay bedtime|ignore_whining[Escape]"
  - "Track sensory triggers that relate to bedtime challenges|sensory_tracking[Sensory]"
  </TabularMCQ>
</TabularMCQGrader>
</CapaProblem>

<Markdown>**Now that you've identified which strategies address escape, which ones would you recommend for Johnny and why?**</Markdown>
<TextArea id="fba2_escape_strategies_done" rows="3" placeholder="Which escape-focused strategies would work best for Johnny?" />
</Vertical>


